	<div class="content">
		<blockquote class="restore"><div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_description">Quote:</div>
	<div class="bbcode_quote printable">
		<hr />
		
			<div>
				Originally Posted by <strong>Goladus</strong>
				<a href="showthread.php?p=1789242#post1789242" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost.gif" alt="View Post" /></a>
			</div>
			<div class="message">Do you guys remember how fucking awesome Everquest was by 2000 or so?  When WoW came out, people basically accepted weekly downtime as a matter of course.  With EQ, people could stay logged in for MONTHS at a time.  That's a huge tell that there was a solid relationship between developers and system administrators.</div>
			
		<hr />
	</div>
</div>Please don't underestimate the problems that arrive with scale. 400k vs millions of customers. Very different beast.</blockquote>
